    But how do you control GameObject activation
    automatically? Conveniently, the GameObject class exposes the function:


    void
    GameObject.SetActive(bool state)

    // Changes to "state" the activation state
    of the GameObject instance it is invoked upon. If it is the first activation
    of the GameObject, its Start() method is run.'
