    m_HorizontalOverflow: 0
    m_VerticalOverflow: 0
    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: "5. EXERCISE 1\n\na) Create a 3D Cube GameObject using the \"GameObject\"
    drop-down menu at the top. \nb) Locate it in the Hierarchy and rename it. \nc)
    Place it anywhere in the scene, using the Move Tool in the Scene tab.\nd) Create
    a script on the empty object and call it \"Localizer\".\ne) We want the script
    to log the transform.position attribute of the object, when it is spawned in
    the scene.\nf) Verify that the logged value matches the position of the object
    Transform, which you may find in the Inspector after selecting the object in
    the Hierarchy.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n"
