  m_Text: "2. MONOBEHAVIOURS\n\nScripts are implemented as subclasses of the MonoBehaviour
    class. The logic of a single MonoBehaviour is defined by overriding various methods
    of this class. For now, we will focus on these two:\n\nvoid Start() \n// This
    method is called once, after any instance of the object is spawned in the scene
    and before calling Update() the first time\n\nvoid Update()\n// This method will
    be called once per frame. In order to coherently maintain the state of the object
    at runtime, we will use class attributes"
