    m_VerticalOverflow: 0
    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: '9. REFERENCING OTHER GAMEOBJECTS


    It is common to implement interaction
    between GameObjects by passing their references in scripts. By declaring public
    GameObject-typed attributes, you will be able to link GameObjects in the scene
    to an instance of a script.


    For an additional level of control over GameObject
    components, use the function:


    T GameObject.GetComponent<T>()

    // Returns
    a reference to the component of type T, of the GameObject that this function
    is invoked upon. If the type of component can be applied multiple times on the
    same object, use GetComponents<T>() to obtain an array of all the components
    of type T on the object.'
