    m_VerticalOverflow: 0
    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: '13. GAMEOBJECT MANAGEMENT


    Besides simply activating/deactivating
    objects, it could be useful to spawn copies of existing GameObjects at runtime.
    Think about games against endless enemy waves, or maybe some procedural effect
    where you randomly add some particular element to the scene.


    On the other
    hand, destroying GameObjects is a far more common necessity, as Unity has no
    "garbage collection" for objects which have completed their life-cycle in the
    virtual world.


'
