    m_HorizontalOverflow: 0
    m_VerticalOverflow: 0
    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: '14. GAMEOBJECT MANAGEMENT


    The two functions employed for these purposes
    are the following. Note that their signatures allow for an Object, meaning you
    can also feed them a Component (in the case of Instantiate, the entire GameObject
    will be cloned as you can''t have two same-type Components).


    Object Instantiate(Object
    original)

    // Returns a clone of "original" and places it into the scene


    void
    Destroy(Object obj)

    // Removes "obj" from the scene. Destruction behaviour
    can be defined in MonoBehaviours by overriding OnDisable() (which also triggers
    on SetActive(false)) and OnDestroy().'
