    m_HorizontalOverflow: 0
    m_VerticalOverflow: 0
    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: "10. EXERCISE 3\n\nSee this can on the right? We're going to give it a
    good kick!\na) Create an empty GameObject, or use an old one from previous exercises\nb)
    Create a new script on the GameObject called \"KickTrigger\"\nc) We need a GameObject
    reference inside the script, that we can set from the inspector\nd) When the
    \"K\" button is pressed, our KickTrigger script should do the following:\n  -Obtain
    the KickIt-typed component from its \n   GameObject reference (step d)\n  -Set
    the \"kick\" attribute of that component to true\ne) Now enter game mode, come
    close so that you can see, and press K!"
