  m_Text: '3. MONOBEHAVIOURS


    In order to create a script, select a GameObject
    from the Hierarchy and press "Add Component" in the Inspector. Type the name
    of your script and press Enter (or "New script"). This will also create a .cs
    code file associated with the component. Double click on the "Script" property
    of the component to edit the script code.


    Inside scripts, you will have
    access to a variety of functions from both the C# and Unity standard libraries.
    For example:


    void Debug.Log(string text)

    // The text you feed to this
    function will be displayed in the Unity console, making it a useful feature for
    debugging.



'
