    m_VerticalOverflow: 0
    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: "6. USER INPUT: KEYBOARD AND MOUSE\n\nIn order to implement interaction
    with the Unity environment, we use the Input library. These are the basic functions:\n\nbool
    Input.GetKey(string name) \n// returns true while button \"name\" is pressed\n\nbool
    Input.GetKeyDown(string name) \n// returns true when button \"name\" is pressed
    and not again until it is released and pressed again\n\nKeyCode\n// enumeration
    containing all button names. Members of this enum can be fed to the functions
    above, e.g.: \nInput.GetKey(KeyCode.Space))"
--- !u!222 &1845094378
