  m_Text: "7. SCRIPT CONFIGURATION\n\nFeeding parameters to a script is a very common
    necessity in Unity. Conveniently, declaring any class attribute of a MonoBehaviour
    as public will allow the user to choose its value from the Inspector. \n\nAs
    an example, go to the \"Main Camera\" object in the Hierarchy and find the \"Movement\"
    script: there, you may edit the speed of movement and rotation for the camera.
    Tweak the values a bit and see how the camera movement changes!"
--- !u!222 &1967891305
