    m_VerticalOverflow: 0
    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: "1. UNITY CODING BASICS\n\nUnity's scripting language is C#. This is an
    object oriented language which is very easy to learn, especially if you happen
    to already know Java. \n\nIn the left column, you will find the hierarchy. This
    menu displays all the objects present in the scene, which are called GameObjects.
    After you select a GameObject, the Inspector (right column) will show the list
    of components of that object.\n\nEach component implements a single behaviour
    of an object. All objects have a Transform, which specifies their position, rotation
    and scale. Unity offers a standard library of pre-implemented behaviour, which
    we will use during the course."
--- !u!222 &2030619211
